This man earned respect and a nickname for leading the 1st Continental Light Dragoons, which
ambushed John Pyle’s Loyalist militia at the Battle of Haw River. This man’s legion was forced to
retreat to Nathanael Greene’s main force at the Battle of Guilford Courthouse after a clash with Banastre
Tarleton. George Washington appointed this man to put down the Whiskey Rebellion. For the point, name
this Revolutionary War soldier, nicknamed “Light-Horse Harry,” who was the father of a Confederate
general.=====
Henry “Light Horse Harry” Lee III =====